Some students doing their Haskell LSystems lab have found that
their program runs out of memory when they try to draw out a 
large LSystem.  You can increase the heap space available to
your program if you start hugs with the following flag at your
linux prompt:

hugs -h2000000 LSystems.hs

There are also two typos on the spec.  On page 7 the 
example:

expand (base 3) (rule 3 ) 3 should be expand (base 3) (rules 3 ) 3 

and

expandOne (expand ( base 3) (rule 3) 3 ) mapper should be
expandOne (expand ( base 3) (rules 3) 3 ) mapper


Thanks,

Peter Cutler




