If you are playing with Haskell graphics and/or are thinking about the
competition...

It has come to my attention that Win32 and Linux versions of the
graphics libraries differ slightly.  The Linux release does not
implement lines completely and I think this translates into pen widths
being ignored.  So, if you try to change the pen size from, say, 1 to 4
nothing will happen under Linux!  It certainly works OK under Win32.

This is a known 'bug' and is mentioned on the haskell.org web site.  I
just hadn't noticed it before!

Enjoy...

Tony.


