Regarding the 'how to do Dijkstra in Haskell' lecture yesterday, I made an omission when discussing solve. The effect of the relaxation process is to refine the shortest path so far for each node once the node with the minimum path has been removed.  However, I believe I omitted to add that having done the relaxation we must then proceed recursively to 'solve' for this relaxed list.  Thus you need to add the call to 'solve' thus:

  :
  where
    :
    solve ps = minp : ( solve ( map relax ( remove minp ps ) ) )
    :

Thanks to the student who spotted this!  Also there is a typo in the 'Common Style Errors' sheet - in 2. fst, snd etc. should all be applied to 'x' not 'xs' as shown.

I hope it helped anyway...

Tony Field.




